    {
      "evidence_id": "ev_fp_1783612457101_6",
      "claim_field": "authentication.auth_summary",
      "claim": "The Podio API uses the OAuth2 protocol for authentication. Developers must register their application to obtain a 'Client ID' and 'Client Secret' (referred to as API keys). Authentication involves different OAuth flows (Server-side, Client-side, Username & password, App authentication) which provide an access token and refresh token. The access token, a bearer token, is included in an 'Authorization: OAuth2 ACCESS_TOKEN' HTTP header.",
      "source_url": "https://developers.podio.com/authentication",
      "source_title": "Authentication - Podio API Documentation",
      "source_type": "developer_portal",
      "evidence_snippet": "The Podio API uses the OAuth2 protocol for authentication. This allows external apps to request authorization to Podio without having direct access to the user's password. Our API supports different OAuth flows depending on what kind of integration you are making.\nBefore you can use the Podio API you must register your application. Your application is assigned a unique identifier, called \"Client ID\", together with a \"Client Secret\". You will need both of these to authenticate.\nPodio supports four different ways of autheticating depending on what kind of application you are building: [Server-side flow](/authentication/server_side), [Client-side flow](/authentication/client_side), [Username & password flow](/authentication/username_password), [App authentication flow](/authentication/app_auth).\nAll of these authentication methods will provide you with an access token. You will be including this access token in any subsequent requests to the API.\n`Authorization: OAuth2 ACCESS_TOKEN`\n\nWhere ACCESS_TOKEN should be replaced with the actual access token you have obtained.\nIn addition to the access token, the response also contains a **expires_in** parameter, and a **refresh_token** parameter.",
      "retrieved_at": "2026-07-09T15:54:17.101Z",
      "supports_claim": false,
      "fetch_mode": "http",
